Outliers|Malcolm Gladwell|Back Bay/Little, Brown|Why some people succeed — it has to do with luck and opportunities as well as talent.
Thinking, Fast And Slow|Daniel Kahneman|Farrar, Straus & Giroux|The winner of the Nobel in economic science discusses how we make choices in business and personal life.
Steve Jobs|Walter Isaacson|Simon & Schuster|A biography of the entrepreneur, based on 40 interviews with Jobs conducted over two years.
Convert Every Click|Benji Rabhan|Wiley|How to increase your business’s Web site profits.
Tipping Point|Malcolm Gladwell|Back Bay/Little Brown|How and why certain products and ideas become fads.
Heads In Beds|Jacob Tomsky|Anchor|A veteran of the hotel industry offers an inside look at the not-always-savory tricks of the trade.
Drive|Daniel H Pink|Riverhead|A look at what truly motivates us, and how we can use that knowledge to work smarter and live better.
Freakonomics|Steven D Levitt,Stephen J Dubner|Harper Perennial|A maverick scholar and a journalist apply economic theory to everything from cheating sumo wrestlers to the falling crime rate.
The Checklist Manifesto|Atul Gawande|Picador|A simple way to manage complexity.
Why Nations Fail|Daron Acemoglu,James A Robinson|Crown Business|How political and economic institutions lead to economic success or failure.
